Project Architecture & Standards

Core Stack

Framework: Next.js 15 (App Router)

Database/Auth: Supabase (PostgreSQL + Auth SSR)

Language: TypeScript (Strict mode)

Source of Truth

Always refer to prd.pdf for feature logic, specific fields, and user flows.

Note: This is a clean Next.js project. No database schema has been built yet. The AI must assist in generating the initial SQL migrations/schema based on the PRD requirements before writing data-fetching code.

Critical Architectural Rules

Route Groups: Organize the app directory into these specific groups:

(marketing): Public-facing pages (Home, About, Contact).

(real-estate): Property listings, search, and construction info.

(travel): Travel services and visa quiz.

(auth): Login, Register, Password Recovery.

(dashboard): Contains nested layouts for /admin, /agent, and /client.

Components: Default to Server Components for data fetching. Use Client Components ('use client') only for interactivity (forms, buttons, real-time filters).

Naming: use kebab-case for directories/files and PascalCase for React components.